Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%g}(chopped lengthways into 1cm slices) lengthways into 1cm
slices, then into 1cm chips (peeling optional). Pop onto a lined #baking tray{}.
Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, cook on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn the tray halfway through.

Once cooked, toss together with the @grated Italian style hard cheese{1%unit}.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Crispy Chicken Burger ==

Place a hand on the @Irish chicken breast{320%g}. Slice horizontally to make two
thin steaks. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Beat the @egg{1%unit} (per 2P) in a #bowl{}.

Season the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} with salt, pepper and the @Italian herbs{1/2%sachet}
(per 2P) in another bowl.

Dip chicken in egg then in breadcrumbs.
> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? This is normal due to packaging
used to keep it fresh.

Place a #pan{} over high heat with just enough oil to coat the bottom. Once hot,
lay the crumbed chicken into the pan.

Reduce the heat to medium-high. Fry until golden brown and cooked through,
~{8-10%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins, adjusting heat if necessary.
> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.
> TIP: Cook in batches if necessary.

== Truffle Sauce ==

Return the empty pan to high heat, adding the @creme fraiche{110%g} and
@chicken stock{1%sachet}.

Cook until thickened, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and stir through the @truffle oil{1%pack}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Cover to keep warm.
> TIP: Loosen with a splash of @?water{to taste} if the sauce becomes too thick.

== Tomato Side Salad ==

Chop the @tomatoes{2%units}(chopped into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks.

Add the tomato to a bowl along with the @salad leaves{40%g}.

Just before serving, toss through the @honey mustard dressing{1%sachet}.

Pop the @brioche buns{2%units} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.
> TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!

== Assembly ==

To assemble the burgers, top each base bun with crispy chicken and a spoonful
of truffle sauce.

Close with the top bun.

Serve the cheesy chips and salad alongside.